sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    %% Flow 1: API Key Authentication (Inference Request)
    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
    Note over Client,ModelBackend: Flow 1: API Key Authentication (Inference Request)

    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as Gateway<br/>maas-default-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PreProc as payload-pre-processing<br/>9004/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>(Kuadrant)
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant PostProc as payload-processing<br/>9004/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant ModelBackend as Model Backend<br/>(KServe / External)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>Auth: Bearer sk-oai-*<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>PreProc: ext_proc (pre-auth)<br/>gRPC/HTTP2, TLS SIMPLE<br/>Extract model name → X-Gateway-Model-Name
    PreProc-->>Gateway: Header: X-Gateway-Model-Name
    Gateway->>Authorino: Auth evaluation<br/>mTLS, internal
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>NetworkPolicy-protected
    MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: SELECT hash, verify SHA-256<br/>TLS, DB credentials
    PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key valid + metadata
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: 200 OK (user identity)
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/subscriptions/select<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>NetworkPolicy-protected
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Selected subscription + rate limit key
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth success + metadata headers
    Gateway->>PostProc: ext_proc (post-auth)<br/>gRPC/HTTP2, TLS SIMPLE<br/>API translation + credential injection
    PostProc-->>Gateway: Transformed request + provider credentials
    Gateway->>ModelBackend: Forward inference request<br/>HTTPS TLS/mTLS<br/>Injected provider credential
    ModelBackend-->>Gateway: Inference response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>TLS 1.2+

    end

    %% Flow 2: Tenant Reconciliation
    rect rgb(245, 255, 245)
    Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Tenant Reconciliation

    participant Controller as maas-controller<br/>(Operator)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Tenant CR<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Tenant CR event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Validate Gateway exists<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Gateway found
    Controller->>Controller: Render kustomize manifests<br/>(embedded in image)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Server-side Apply:<br/>maas-api Deployment, Service,<br/>HTTPRoute, NetworkPolicies,<br/>PodMonitor, AuthPolicy,<br/>TokenRateLimitPolicy<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources applied

    end

    %% Flow 3: External Model Routing
    rect rgb(255, 245, 238)
    Note over Controller,ExternalLLM: Flow 3: External Model Routing

    participant ExternalLLM as External LLM Provider<br/>(OpenAI, Anthropic)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch ExternalModel CR<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: ExternalModel event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ExternalName Service<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Istio ServiceEntry<br/>(register provider in mesh)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Istio DestinationRule<br/>(TLS origination)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute<br/>(per-model routing)
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources created

    Note over Gateway,ExternalLLM: Runtime: inference traffic flows through gateway
    Gateway->>ExternalLLM: Forward via ServiceEntry<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>API key injected by payload-processing

    end
